  "name": "New York City",
  "notes": "DSNY runs a multi-bin system: (1) Metal/Glass/Plastic/Cartons (MGP) and (2) Mixed Paper/Cardboard set out as separate clear bags or labeled bins on recycling day; (3) Curbside Composting (brown bin or labeled bin) — MANDATORY citywide as of April 1, 2025 for food scraps, food-soiled paper, and all yard waste; (4) Trash. NYC does not enforce a 3-inch minimum size or distinguish plastic resin codes — any rigid plastic is recyclable. Cartons go with MGP, not paper. Lightly-soiled pizza boxes are accepted in paper recycling; greasy ones go to compost. CFC appliances (AC units, refrigerators) require special handling before pickup. Single-family-home assumption; multi-family and 10+ unit buildings have additional storage and set-out rules.",
  "primary_source": "https://www.nyc.gov/site/dsny/collection/get-rid-of.page",
